OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBAME acronym: UK           
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbroadcasters commit to     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Favoiding catch-all term    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, UK broadcasters have committed to      
OL,6, avoiding the use of the acronym BAME   
OL,7, "wherever possible" following the      
OL,8, publication of an industry report.     
OL,10,FThe catch-all description for black,   
OL,11,FAsian and minority ethnic people will  
OL,12,Fbe ditched in favour of the use of more
OL,13,Fspecific terms to describe ethnicity.  
OL,15,FThe BBC, ITV, Channel 4 and Channel 5  
OL,16,Fwelcomed the findings from the Sir     
OL,17,FLenny Henry Centre for Media Diversity.
OL,19,FThe report concluded there "was a lack 
OL,20,Fof trust" around the term BAME.        
